observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

a) Municipal Engineer to exhaust measures to provide the Municipal Accountant and Municipal GSO-Designate with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for other road projects which are still not accounted;

b) Inventory Committee/ Municipal GSO-Designate to conduct inventory count of all the Municipalitys road network systems and accordingly submit a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System as of the end of the year and complete the necessary information in the RLRN;

c) Municipal Accountant and Municipal GSO-Designate to reconcile the difference noted between the balance of Road Networks as per books of accounts and as per RLRN;

d) Municipal Accountant, Municipal GSO-Designate and Municipal Engineer to account the unrecorded Road Networks before the effectivity of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and

e) Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the prescribed property ledger cards for Local Road Networks and disclose all the required information for the said property in the Notes to Financial Statements.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:

a) Concerned official to provide justification of hiring an event coordinator even if without selection process in accordance with Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;

b) The Municipal Accountant to submit the noted lacking documents for further evaluation showing the following:

i. Assessment of the Municipality that the services of an event coordinator are not within their in-house capability;

ii. Written pre-set qualifications standards/policies/guidelines for the hiring of event coordinator;

iii. Proven expertise, experience and capability of the hired event coordinator;

iv. Terms of Reference or documents indicating the expected outputs/deliverables of the event coordinator;

v. Copy of APP showing the procurement for event coordinator; and

vi. Accomplishment reports.

Likewise, we recommended adhering to the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 in the hiring of event coordinator/planner and ensuring that documents that will prove the expertise, track records, performances, compliance to laws, etc. of the prospective event coordinator/planner are submitted and validated.

We further recommended that the Management refrains from incurring unnecessary expenditures and channel its resources to the implementation of projects and programs which are more beneficial to the constituents of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

a) Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Office (MENRO) to acquire a written contract between the Municipality and private sanitary landfill company covering the period for services from April to November 2019 in the amount of P163,429.00 to protect the interest of the Municipality and for further evaluation of the Audit Team;

b) MENRO to provide justification for further evaluation of the Audit Team on availing the services of the private sanitary landfill even it did not pass through proper selection process in accordance with Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;

c) Municipal Accountant to ensure that the disbursements are supported with complete documents and appropriate taxes has been withheld before certifying to that effect; and

d) BAC to ensure that the Municipality complies with the procurement process of selection of private sanitary landfill under RA No. 9184 and its Revised IRR.

We recommended that the City Mayor instruct the GSO to:
• conduct detailed review of the documents maintained to determine the correct classification of each PPE for the consequent classification and adjustments to ensure the accuracy of the inventory and accounting records; 
• direct the concerned personnel concerned to reconcile the result of the physical count of all PPE with the property and accounting records and submit in the prescribed form the RPCPPE and submit to the Auditor not later than January 31, of each year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct 
the GAD Focal Point Persons to ensure that the program/projects/ activities be supported with sex-disaggregated data and gender analysis and its intended outcome lead to empowerment and protection of women and girl-children for such program/activity to be funded out of GAD budget;

the Local officials and employees concerned to promote and ensure that gender and development is mainstreamed in local-policy making, planning, programming and budgeting;

the concerned officials to make sure that their GAD Focal Point System or similar GAD mechanisms are in place, fully-functional and the members have the capacity and influence to promote gender mainstreaming pursuant to Section 37 of the Magna Carta of Women Implementing Rules and Regulations; and

 the Focal Point Person to check on the compliance to all procedural and reporting requirements of Joint            Memorandum (JMC) No.  2013-01 and establish and strengthen their monitoring and evaluation systems to assess the effectiveness and efficiency of their gender mainstreaming efforts.
